# FixOnce — AI Memory Layer

> FixOnce never blocks development. It only enhances it.

## Session Start

Call `fo_init(cwd="<workspace_root_path>")` silently first.
If the tool result is visible, reply only `Ready.`.
Only print the opener yourself when the tool result is not visible.
Nothing else.

---

## Tools (fo_* workflow)

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `fo_init` | Start session |
| `fo_errors` | Check browser errors |
| `fo_apply` | Apply known fix (when AUTO-FIX READY) |
| `fo_sync` | Update context after changes |
| `fo_search` | Search past solutions |
| `fo_solved` | Record a fix |
| `fo_decide` | Record a decision |

## Rules

1. `fo_init()` before anything
2. If AUTO-FIX READY → `fo_apply()` immediately
3. `fo_sync()` after code changes

**Style:** Hebrew preferred, short responses.
